TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed HttpStatusCode extends System.Enum

Docs.summary: Contains the values of status codes defined for HTTP.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The HttpStatusCode enumeration contains the values of the status codes defined in RFC 2616 for HTTP 1.1.
The status of an HTTP request is contained in the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebResponse.StatusCode%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
## Examples The following example compares the status returned by an <xref:System.Net.HttpWebResponse> with a member of the HttpStatusCode class to determine the status of a response.
[!code-cs[Classic HttpStatusCode Example#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.net.httpstatusc_1.cs)] [!code-vb[Classic HttpStatusCode Example#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.net.httpstatusc_1.vb)] [!code-cpp[Classic HttpStatusCode Example#1](~/add/codesnippet/cpp/t-system.net.httpstatusc_1.cpp)]

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Accepted = int32(202)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 202. Accepted indicates that the request has been accepted for further processing.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Ambiguous = int32(300)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 300. Ambiguous indicates that the requested information has multiple representations. The default action is to treat this status as a redirect and follow the contents of the Location header associated with this response.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, Ambiguous will cause an exception to be thrown.
Ambiguous is a synonym for MultipleChoices.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode BadGateway = int32(502)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 502. BadGateway indicates that an intermediate proxy server received a bad response from another proxy or the origin server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode BadRequest = int32(400)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 400. BadRequest indicates that the request could not be understood by the server. BadRequest is sent when no other error is applicable, or if the exact error is unknown or does not have its own error code.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Conflict = int32(409)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 409. Conflict indicates that the request could not be carried out because of a conflict on the server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Continue = int32(100)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 100. Continue indicates that the client can continue with its request.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Created = int32(201)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 201. Created indicates that the request resulted in a new resource created before the response was sent.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode ExpectationFailed = int32(417)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 417. ExpectationFailed indicates that an expectation given in an Expect header could not be met by the server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Forbidden = int32(403)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 403. Forbidden indicates that the server refuses to fulfill the request.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Found = int32(302)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 302. Found indicates that the requested information is located at the URI specified in the Location header. The default action when this status is received is to follow the Location header associated with the response. When the original request method was POST, the redirected request will use the GET method.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, Found will cause an exception to be thrown.
Found is a synonym for Redirect.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode GatewayTimeout = int32(504)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 504. GatewayTimeout indicates that an intermediate proxy server timed out while waiting for a response from another proxy or the origin server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Gone = int32(410)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 410. Gone indicates that the requested resource is no longer available.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode HttpVersionNotSupported = int32(505)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 505. HttpVersionNotSupported indicates that the requested HTTP version is not supported by the server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode InternalServerError = int32(500)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 500. InternalServerError indicates that a generic error has occurred on the server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode LengthRequired = int32(411)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 411. LengthRequired indicates that the required Content-length header is missing.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode MethodNotAllowed = int32(405)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 405. MethodNotAllowed indicates that the request method (POST or GET) is not allowed on the requested resource.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Moved = int32(301)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 301. Moved indicates that the requested information has been moved to the URI specified in the Location header. The default action when this status is received is to follow the Location header associated with the response. When the original request method was POST, the redirected request will use the GET method.

remarks.format: ## Remarks Moved is a synonym for MovedPermanently.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode MovedPermanently = int32(301)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 301. MovedPermanently indicates that the requested information has been moved to the URI specified in the Location header. The default action when this status is received is to follow the Location header associated with the response.

remarks.format: ## Remarks MovedPermanently is a synonym for Moved.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode MultipleChoices = int32(300)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 300. MultipleChoices indicates that the requested information has multiple representations. The default action is to treat this status as a redirect and follow the contents of the Location header associated with this response.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, MultipleChoices will cause an exception to be thrown.
MultipleChoices is a synonym for Ambiguous.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode NoContent = int32(204)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 204. NoContent indicates that the request has been successfully processed and that the response is intentionally blank.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode NonAuthoritativeInformation = int32(203)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 203. NonAuthoritativeInformation indicates that the returned metainformation is from a cached copy instead of the origin server and therefore may be incorrect.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode NotAcceptable = int32(406)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 406. NotAcceptable indicates that the client has indicated with Accept headers that it will not accept any of the available representations of the resource.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode NotFound = int32(404)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 404. NotFound indicates that the requested resource does not exist on the server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode NotImplemented = int32(501)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 501. NotImplemented indicates that the server does not support the requested function.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode NotModified = int32(304)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 304. NotModified indicates that the client's cached copy is up to date. The contents of the resource are not transferred.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode OK = int32(200)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 200. OK indicates that the request succeeded and that the requested information is in the response. This is the most common status code to receive.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode PartialContent = int32(206)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 206. PartialContent indicates that the response is a partial response as requested by a GET request that includes a byte range.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode PaymentRequired = int32(402)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 402. PaymentRequired is reserved for future use.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode PreconditionFailed = int32(412)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 412. PreconditionFailed indicates that a condition set for this request failed, and the request cannot be carried out. Conditions are set with conditional request headers like If-Match, If-None-Match, or If-Unmodified-Since.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode ProxyAuthenticationRequired = int32(407)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 407. ProxyAuthenticationRequired indicates that the requested proxy requires authentication. The Proxy-authenticate header contains the details of how to perform the authentication.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Redirect = int32(302)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 302. Redirect indicates that the requested information is located at the URI specified in the Location header. The default action when this status is received is to follow the Location header associated with the response. When the original request method was POST, the redirected request will use the GET method.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, Redirect will cause an exception to be thrown.
Redirect is a synonym for Found.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode RedirectKeepVerb = int32(307)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 307. RedirectKeepVerb indicates that the request information is located at the URI specified in the Location header. The default action when this status is received is to follow the Location header associated with the response. When the original request method was POST, the redirected request will also use the POST method.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, RedirectKeepVerb will cause an exception to be thrown.
RedirectKeepVerb is a synonym for TemporaryRedirect.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode RedirectMethod = int32(303)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 303. RedirectMethod automatically redirects the client to the URI specified in the Location header as the result of a POST. The request to the resource specified by the Location header will be made with a GET.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, RedirectMethod will cause an exception to be thrown.
RedirectMethod is a synonym for SeeOther.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode RequestedRangeNotSatisfiable = int32(416)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 416. RequestedRangeNotSatisfiable indicates that the range of data requested from the resource cannot be returned, either because the beginning of the range is before the beginning of the resource, or the end of the range is after the end of the resource.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode RequestEntityTooLarge = int32(413)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 413. RequestEntityTooLarge indicates that the request is too large for the server to process.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode RequestTimeout = int32(408)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 408. RequestTimeout indicates that the client did not send a request within the time the server was expecting the request.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode RequestUriTooLong = int32(414)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 414. RequestUriTooLong indicates that the URI is too long.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode ResetContent = int32(205)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 205. ResetContent indicates that the client should reset (not reload) the current resource.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode SeeOther = int32(303)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 303. SeeOther automatically redirects the client to the URI specified in the Location header as the result of a POST. The request to the resource specified by the Location header will be made with a GET.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, SeeOther will cause an exception to be thrown.
SeeOther is a synonym for RedirectMethod.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode ServiceUnavailable = int32(503)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 503. ServiceUnavailable indicates that the server is temporarily unavailable, usually due to high load or maintenance.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode SwitchingProtocols = int32(101)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 101. SwitchingProtocols indicates that the protocol version or protocol is being changed.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode TemporaryRedirect = int32(307)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 307. TemporaryRedirect indicates that the request information is located at the URI specified in the Location header. The default action when this status is received is to follow the Location header associated with the response. When the original request method was POST, the redirected request will also use the POST method.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is `false`, TemporaryRedirect will cause an exception to be thrown.
TemporaryRedirect is a synonym for RedirectKeepVerb.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Unauthorized = int32(401)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 401. Unauthorized indicates that the requested resource requires authentication. The WWW-Authenticate header contains the details of how to perform the authentication.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode UnsupportedMediaType = int32(415)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 415. UnsupportedMediaType indicates that the request is an unsupported type.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Unused = int32(306)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 306. Unused is a proposed extension to the HTTP/1.1 specification that is not fully specified.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode UpgradeRequired = int32(426)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 426. UpgradeRequired indicates that the client should switch to a different protocol such as TLS/1.0.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode UseProxy = int32(305)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 305. UseProxy indicates that the request should use the proxy server at the URI specified in the Location header.
